text: The Satpute Koli, or Sutpute Koli is a clan of Koli caste found in the Indian state of Maharashtra. The Kolis of Satpute clan revolted against British rule in Maharashtra under their Koli chief Sakharam Satpute and captured the British offices and plundered the British controlled Territories in Konkan. == See also == * List of Koli titles, clans and subcastes == References == Category:Koli clans
title: Satpute Koli
